  <field name="Date range" metaFormat="osm" metaVersion="1.1" language="en-us" path="/record/coverage/dateRange">
  <!--KEEP: Use the base of xs:string so that in the Digital Collections System (DCS) no data entry box appears for date but data entry boxes will appear for start and end attributes.-->
		<definition></definition> 

		 <bestPractices>
			<dos>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">This field is optional field but should be completed as described below.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">This field can be repeated.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">At a minimum, the type and start date information must be completed.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Use this field for completing event information for presentations/webcasts, posters and proceedings articles.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Use this field for completing dates associated with correspondence or interviews.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Use this field for creating embargoes on resources when they can not be made accessible to the public for a certain amount of time.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Consult with SHERPA/RoMEO to identify any applicable embargo periods.</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Due to a UCAR special agreement, AMS and AGU each have embargoes of 6 months, regardless of what SHERPA/RoMEO indicates.</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">The Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society (BAMS) never has an embargo.</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Due to a UCAR special agreement, Springer does not impose an embargo on UCAR/NCAR/UCP publications as long as the publication date is before 2014.</practice>
			 </dos>
		 </bestPractices>
